394
00:30:02,892 --> 00:30:04,011
Of course.

395
00:30:04,412 --> 00:30:05,932
The wine is hardly
as precious as the kids.

396
00:30:07,612 --> 00:30:09,011
Don't fuss about the wine.

397
00:30:10,011 --> 00:30:11,811
The kids must be hungry
from the long trip.

398
00:30:11,852 --> 00:30:12,771
We should eat first.

399
00:30:12,932 --> 00:30:14,331
Yes, fill your stomach.

400
00:30:14,692 --> 00:30:16,172
This is my specialty soup.

401
00:30:16,571 --> 00:30:17,051
And this too.

402
00:30:17,051 --> 00:30:17,612
Thanks, ma'am.

403
00:30:17,811 --> 00:30:18,452
Lotus.

404
00:30:19,372 --> 00:30:20,132
Daiwen said

405
00:30:20,331 --> 00:30:21,452
pot-fried pork is your favorite.

406
00:30:23,811 --> 00:30:24,571
Go on, eat.

407
00:30:24,692 --> 00:30:25,612
Try the food I made.

408
00:30:26,091 --> 00:30:26,571
Okay.

409
00:30:35,410 --> 00:30:36,120
What's the matter?

410
00:30:36,652 --> 00:30:37,612
Is it not to your taste?

411
00:30:40,212 --> 00:30:40,811
No, no.

412
00:30:56,731 --> 00:30:57,531
What's wrong?

413
00:31:03,811 --> 00:31:04,731
It's nothing, ma'am.

414
00:31:05,051 --> 00:31:05,852
It's very good.

415
00:31:12,331 --> 00:31:12,731
What?

416
00:31:13,892 --> 00:31:14,612
What's the matter?

417
00:31:15,051 --> 00:31:15,852
You can tell me.

418
00:31:19,692 --> 00:31:20,251
Ma'am...

419
00:31:21,972 --> 00:31:22,972
Your cooking

420
00:31:23,372 --> 00:31:24,251
is too delicious.

421
00:31:25,892 --> 00:31:27,172
It's just like my mom's cooking.

422
00:31:31,291 --> 00:31:32,251
It's like her mom's.

423
00:31:33,112 --> 00:31:34,090
You should eat more then.

424
00:31:34,291 --> 00:31:35,372
Yes, eat more.

425
00:31:36,491 --> 00:31:36,892
Daiwen.

426
00:31:38,291 --> 00:31:38,692
Daiwen.

427
00:31:40,452 --> 00:31:41,652
My mom...

428
00:31:43,091 --> 00:31:43,731
My mom

429
00:31:44,692 --> 00:31:45,491
just passed away.

430
00:32:05,811 --> 00:32:06,212
Yi.

431
00:32:10,091 --> 00:32:11,091
Sorry for your loss.

432
00:32:12,771 --> 00:32:13,531
I

433
00:32:14,212 --> 00:32:15,692
understand how you feel right now.

434
00:32:17,811 --> 00:32:19,251
I've lost my parents too.

435
00:32:20,331 --> 00:32:21,491
I also lost my loved one.

436
00:32:22,571 --> 00:32:24,692
Losing people you love
is part and parcel of life.

437
00:32:26,731 --> 00:32:27,731
You'll probably never

438
00:32:28,452 --> 00:32:29,412
come to terms with it.

439
00:32:31,172 --> 00:32:33,091
We may not be able to turn back time,

440
00:32:33,091 --> 00:32:33,892
but,

441
00:32:35,051 --> 00:32:37,011
we have to accept reality
and move forward.

442
00:32:39,212 --> 00:32:40,811
I told Daiwen the same.

443
00:32:42,412 --> 00:32:43,412
It's no good

444
00:32:44,172 --> 00:32:45,692
only to remember what tore us apart.

445
00:32:47,011 --> 00:32:48,132
What we should remember

446
00:32:48,932 --> 00:32:50,972
is the time we spent together, right?

447
00:32:56,972 --> 00:32:58,531
People say parents

448
00:32:58,612 --> 00:32:59,892
are like angels manifested.

449
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:02,530
There's no need to put so much emphasis

450
00:33:02,972 --> 00:33:03,692
on life and death.

451
00:33:04,331 --> 00:33:05,612
What really matters is

452
00:33:07,531 --> 00:33:08,771
they're never far away.

453
00:33:18,612 --> 00:33:18,932
Here.

454
00:33:19,352 --> 00:33:20,824
Let's raise our glasses to your mother.

455
00:33:22,652 --> 00:33:23,692
Death is just a long journey.

456
00:33:24,932 --> 00:33:25,852
You'll meet again one day.

457
00:33:40,412 --> 00:33:40,852
Eat more.

458
00:33:42,452 --> 00:33:43,132
Come, have more meat.

459
00:33:43,692 --> 00:33:44,291
Try this dish.

460
00:33:45,091 --> 00:33:45,452
Okay.

461
00:33:49,811 --> 00:33:51,692
She bought this from the supermarket.

462
00:33:52,331 --> 00:33:54,571
Don't be sly. I made this myself.

463
00:33:54,571 --> 00:33:55,051
Yes, sure.

464
00:33:55,051 --> 00:33:55,571
Eat more.

465
00:33:55,571 --> 00:33:56,091
You made it.

466
00:33:56,531 --> 00:33:57,331
Eat more.

467
00:33:57,400 --> 00:33:58,010
You too, Daiwen.

468
00:33:58,011 --> 00:33:58,491
Here.

469
00:34:00,972 --> 00:34:02,051
Daiwen, have the lotus.

470
00:34:02,051 --> 00:34:02,892
Is it good?

471
00:34:03,132 --> 00:34:04,531
It has to be good since it's bought.

472
00:34:04,612 --> 00:34:06,652
No, I mean, she made it.

473
00:34:45,732 --> 00:34:46,571
Liang Daiwen.

474
00:34:49,691 --> 00:34:50,372
Can you

475
00:34:50,972 --> 00:34:52,571
tell me

476
00:34:53,051 --> 00:34:54,011
about your mom?

477
00:35:00,892 --> 00:35:02,412
I don't quite remember

478
00:35:05,091 --> 00:35:06,452
a lot of the details now.

479
00:35:07,571 --> 00:35:08,691
I can't tell

480
00:35:10,571 --> 00:35:12,932
if certain memories actually happened

481
00:35:14,611 --> 00:35:15,852
or if I conjured them.

482
00:35:20,732 --> 00:35:21,412
That's okay.

483
00:35:22,372 --> 00:35:24,091
You can tell me what you remember.

484
00:35:25,051 --> 00:35:25,972
I'd like to hear it.

485
00:35:41,611 --> 00:35:42,651
I remember my mom

486
00:35:45,011 --> 00:35:45,852
laughed a lot.

487
00:35:49,352 --> 00:35:50,850
She looked beautiful when she smiled.

488
00:35:54,691 --> 00:35:56,292
She was very active before she got ill.

489
00:35:57,368 --> 00:35:58,264
Hiking mountains,

490
00:35:58,972 --> 00:35:59,491
dancing,

491
00:36:00,611 --> 00:36:01,051
and swimming.

492
00:36:02,171 --> 00:36:02,892
She did them all.

493
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:06,040
She was really good at drawing too.

494
00:36:07,292 --> 00:36:08,091
She knew

495
00:36:09,252 --> 00:36:10,772
how to fix my dad's designs.

496
00:36:12,852 --> 00:36:13,972
She was always hands-on.

497
00:36:15,252 --> 00:36:16,211
When we went to the beach,

498
00:36:17,452 --> 00:36:18,691
she'd help me build

499
00:36:19,491 --> 00:36:21,131
those really cool sandcastles.

500
00:36:30,772 --> 00:36:32,171
But when she got sick,

501
00:36:33,372 --> 00:36:34,491
she hardly went outside.

502
00:36:37,772 --> 00:36:39,051
Most of the time,

503
00:36:41,691 --> 00:36:43,011
she'd sit by the window

504
00:36:44,812 --> 00:36:45,571
and look out.

505
00:36:49,171 --> 00:36:50,732
My dad worried
she might become depressed

506
00:36:52,252 --> 00:36:54,252
and so he bought lots of plants

507
00:36:55,128 --> 00:36:56,290
and placed them on the balcony.

508
00:37:01,171 --> 00:37:02,171
But she was like you.

509
00:37:03,972 --> 00:37:05,211
She couldn't even keep a cactus alive.

510
00:37:08,171 --> 00:37:10,452
She used to love watching horror films.

511
00:37:15,691 --> 00:37:16,852
I was a cowardly kid.

512
00:37:18,760 --> 00:37:19,650
I had lots of fears.

513
00:37:23,732 --> 00:37:25,091
So I never watched it with her.

514
00:37:31,452 --> 00:37:32,491
But after she passed,

515
00:37:34,812 --> 00:37:36,051
I somehow became unafraid.

516
00:37:38,690 --> 00:37:39,704
I wasn't afraid of the dark.

517
00:37:42,651 --> 00:37:43,571
Nor afraid of ghosts.

518
00:37:47,560 --> 00:37:48,850
I was no longer afraid of anything.

519
00:37:57,412 --> 00:37:58,491
I just really missed her.

520
00:38:00,972 --> 00:38:01,812
Missed her awfully.

521
00:38:05,171 --> 00:38:06,091
I would often

522
00:38:06,651 --> 00:38:08,211
go to the cemetery at night.

523
00:38:11,252 --> 00:38:12,412
I wanted to see

524
00:38:12,892 --> 00:38:13,972
if I could see her.

525
00:38:24,332 --> 00:38:25,651
But I never once saw anything.

526
00:38:41,732 --> 00:38:42,412
Liang Daiwen.

527
00:38:44,732 --> 00:38:45,571
Can you

528
00:38:46,131 --> 00:38:47,691
take me to see your mom tomorrow?

529
00:39:09,788 --> 00:39:14,475
(Tomb of loving mother, Zhou Dai)

530
00:39:17,452 --> 00:39:17,852
Mom.

531
00:39:21,491 --> 00:39:22,691
I brought my girlfriend to see you.

532
00:39:28,332 --> 00:39:28,972
Hello, ma'am.

533
00:39:30,452 --> 00:39:33,252
I am Liang Daiwen's girlfriend, Gu Yi.

534
00:39:35,051 --> 00:39:36,051
My apologies,

535
00:39:36,252 --> 00:39:37,651
for only coming to see you now.

536
00:39:40,131 --> 00:39:41,892
Liang Daiwen has grown up
to be a great person.

537
00:39:42,611 --> 00:39:45,051
He's tall, handsome and healthy.

538
00:39:46,011 --> 00:39:48,531
He's doing what he loves,
which is accessible design.

539
00:39:50,171 --> 00:39:51,252
Besides him,

540
00:39:52,452 --> 00:39:54,211
there's me and a bunch of friends
who adore him.

541
00:39:55,571 --> 00:39:56,571
So rest assured.

542
00:39:58,091 --> 00:39:59,412
The only bummer

543
00:40:00,292 --> 00:40:01,812
is that he really misses you.

544
00:40:04,051 --> 00:40:04,732
Liang Daiwen,

545
00:40:06,171 --> 00:40:08,171
should we let your mom listen

546
00:40:08,651 --> 00:40:10,051
to the message my mom left for you?

547
00:40:22,171 --> 00:40:22,852
Liang.

548
00:40:24,611 --> 00:40:26,091
I'm sorry I can no longer

549
00:40:26,131 --> 00:40:27,732
speak to you face to face.

550
00:40:30,252 --> 00:40:32,171
Consider this a few words of advice

551
00:40:33,372 --> 00:40:34,972
from your future mother-in-law.

552
00:40:36,571 --> 00:40:38,252
I'm glad Gu Yi is in your care.

553
00:40:40,491 --> 00:40:42,571
My wish is for you two
to be happy and well.

554
00:40:44,932 --> 00:40:46,732
But don't feel pressured by it.

555
00:40:48,452 --> 00:40:49,011
After all,

556
00:40:50,412 --> 00:40:51,892
it's up to you

557
00:40:52,691 --> 00:40:53,972
how you want to live.

558
00:40:55,091 --> 00:40:57,531
Whether you stay together
or go separate ways,

559
00:40:59,252 --> 00:41:02,011
I hope you'll always have
the other's best interest at heart.

560
00:41:03,932 --> 00:41:05,051
Don't let the other person down.

